<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><listPerson xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><person xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="CAR06" sex="1"><persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><roleName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"/><forename xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">John Aitken</forename><surname xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Carlyle</surname><addName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Jack</addName></persName><birth xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1801-07-07"><placeName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"> </placeName></birth><death xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1879-09-15"/><occupation xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">physician</occupation><occupation xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">writer</occupation><note xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="editorial"><p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">John was the brother of <persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" key="CAR03">Thomas Carlyle</persName>. He graduated MD from the University of Edinburgh in 1826. He later tried to earn a living 
    from writing in London. He attended <persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" key="HAZ01">William Hazlitt</persName> when Hazlitt was dying. He spent a number of years working as a travelling physician to 
